page.title: 02PLANT LIFE ON RANMORE COMMON
page.content:
CHALK SCARP ___________ Part of the walk,as far as the Spains follows the course of the famous Pilgrims' Way.Species found on a very hot and dry summer day 6th July 1985 were:_
Bee Orchid,Ophrys Apifera. Man Orchid,Aceras Anthropophorum. Pyramidal Orchid,Anacamptis Pyramidalis. Cowslip,Primula Veris. Ox_Eye Daisy,Chrysanthemum Levcanthemum. Primrose,Primula Vulgaris. Common Wild Thyme,Thymus Drucei. Larger Wild Thyme,Thymus Pulegioides. Kidney Vetch,Anthyllis Vulmeraria. Milk Wort Chalk,Polygala Calcarea. Tufted Vetch,Vici Cracco Rock Rose,Helianthemum Nummularium.
